article.headline: Stetson 78, Flagler 56
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Sophomore guard E.J. Gordon scored 19 points and four other Stetson players reached double figures in the Hatters' 78-56 victory over Flagler on Friday. Gordon, the Atlantic Sun Conference Freshman of the Year last season, reached double figures for the 16th consecutive game. He also grabbed a game-high eight rebounds. Josef McNeal and Mark Stiles each had 13 points for Stetson (1-0), which enjoyed its widest victory margin in two full seasons. Stetson led by as many as 33 points in the second half. Flagler guard John Randolph led all scorers with 24 points, and added seven rebounds. Flagler (4-1) is an NAIA school which made its season debut against NCAA Division I competition.
